---
import GuidedCommandPreview from "./blog/GuidedCommandPreview";
---

<div class="not-prose my-10 rounded-[2rem] border border-base-300 bg-base-100 p-5 shadow-sm sm:p-7">
  <div class="space-y-2">
    <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.25em] text-accent">
      Live Wasm Demo
    </p>
    <h3 class="m-0 text-2xl font-semibold text-base-content">
      A guided version of the real command flow
    </h3>
    <p class="m-0 max-w-3xl text-sm leading-6 text-base-content/70">
      Rather than asking the reader to play with a tiny level, this demo offers
      a few real commands discovered from the browser-local engine. Selecting a
      card shows the preview branch, and committing it promotes that future into
      live history.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="mt-5 grid gap-3 md:grid-cols-3">
    <div class="rounded-2xl bg-base-200/70 p-4">
      <p class="m-0 text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-base-content/50">
        Select
      </p>
      <p class="m-0 mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-base-content/70">
        Inspect a real preview branch without mutating the active snapshot.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="rounded-2xl bg-base-200/70 p-4">
      <p class="m-0 text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-base-content/50">
        Commit
      </p>
      <p class="m-0 mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-base-content/70">
        Promote the selected future into tracked history using the same command.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="rounded-2xl bg-base-200/70 p-4">
      <p class="m-0 text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-base-content/50">
        Reset
      </p>
      <p class="m-0 mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-base-content/70">
        Return to the seeded world and try a different branch.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="mt-5">
    <GuidedCommandPreview client:load />
  </div>
</div>
